description: Baby sonic goes to the park with his mom, sibs, and uncle chuck to have a picnic.  He expects to only eat food and have fun, but things don't go as planned when he runs into Bartleby montclair of dresdin. Another baby that he has a crush on. Will this love bossom or die out like a spark?

replies.text: ​ @yeechster 8008  what the fuck are you fucking talking about. this episode explores new territory while tying back into an old plot line from the cereal episode. For the first time in this shows history Bartlby Montclair is vulnerable, petty and weak only to restore his grace in the same fucking episode. A character who towered over the rest of the cast with his magnanimity falls flat on his bare fucking ass and is defeated. yet with the grace of a caeser accepts his faults and returns his composure not but minutes later. The assassination attempt flawlessy connects this theme of grace, as bartlby even at his weakest still maintains a compsure that allows him to out guile the trickery of an entire "support" network around him AS A FUCKING BABY. it is also heavily implied not just in this episode but in many others that themes of homophobia are progressively coming to light. I don't know if you are retarded or what but this is a fantastic take on the theme of the dark night of the soul with great pacing and subtle psychology, it really is a pitiable shame you can't see that you absolute fucking mongoloid.
